# git-allowed-signers file for verifying Looptimal's SSH-signed tags/commits.
#
# This is the maintainer's PUBLIC key only (safe to publish — it's already public via
# GitHub's own "SSH signing keys" page for the account, and every SSH-signed commit/tag
# on this repo already carries it). It grants no write access to anything; it only lets
# `git verify-tag`/`git verify-commit` confirm a tag or commit was actually signed by
# this key, instead of erroring with "allowedSignersFile needs to be configured."
#
# Usage:
#   git config gpg.ssh.allowedSignersFile "$(pwd)/allowed_signers.example"
#   git verify-tag v2.0.0
#   git verify-commit <sha>
#
# Format: <principal(s)> <key-type> <base64-key>  (see `man ssh-keygen` -Y verify / gpg.ssh docs)
113260749+Rennlabs@users.noreply.github.com ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIGMQu4u13T0ZCz00OGvcEXFk4zVJcVwB+gIaJD7Qs1El
